QUIC is Google's experimental, low-latency Internet transportation protocol over UDP, a protocol that is often used by gaming, streaming media and VoIP services
• Networks → Network protocol design; Transport protocols; Cross-layer protocols;
 QUIC
replaces most of the traditional HTTPS stack: HTTP/2, TLS.
transfer of 2 layers of handshakes (initial -> final) between the IP and the server.
